From 28e53e7ad30f0af70747536077c3053cd738db74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ahmed AbdEl-Kareem <ahmed1abdalkrem1@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 23:31:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: remove offline page blocking login + complete mobile
 responsiveness
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CRITICAL FIXES (login & navigation):
- Removed navigateFallback offline.html — this was intercepting Google OAuth
  callback navigation and showing 'you are offline' even when connected
- Deleted frontend/public/offline.html entirely (no longer used)
- Removed offline.html from PWA includeAssets
- Added skipWaiting + clientsClaim so all users get the fix immediately
- Excluded /auth/google paths from API response caching (was interfering
  with OAuth redirect flow)
- Fixed API cache urlPattern to exclude localhost explicitly

FONT FIX:
- Removed dead Cairo v28 font preload link (404, Google moved to v31+)
  This was the source of the 'preloaded but not used' console warning

MOBILE RESPONSIVENESS — COMPLETE OVERHAUL:
- Sidebar: now uses Framer Motion x-axis slide + fixed positioning on mobile
  (was using width-only animation that never worked on small screens)
- Sidebar: added isMobile state with resize listener for correct behavior
- Sidebar: added dark backdrop overlay that closes sidebar on tap
- Sidebar: dynamic 'open' className so CSS rules apply correctly
- Fixed 29 grid layout instances across 21 component files — all
  minmax(Xpx, 1fr) patterns now use minmax(min(Xpx,100%), 1fr) so grids
  properly collapse to 1 column on narrow screens instead of overflowing
- Fixed 3 two-column 'sidebar+content' layouts (Files, Profile, Notes)
  that used fixed pixel widths — now stack vertically below 768px
- Rewrote global.css mobile media queries: removed conflicting transform
  rules, added complete mobile system (overflow prevention, 16px inputs
  to prevent iOS zoom, touch target sizing, modal sizing, responsive
  typography with clamp())
- main-content now properly fills 100% width on mobile/tablet regardless
  of sidebar state (was shifting/shrinking before)

Verified with production build: 'vite build' completes with zero errors,
generated service worker confirmed to have zero references to offline.html
